  "prompt": "Who whave my number on watsapp?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, there isn't a built-in feature in WhatsApp that allows you to see a list of all the people who have your number saved. However, you can infer who has your number in a few ways:\n\n1. **Broadcast Message**: You could send a broadcast message. Only contacts who have your number saved will receive the message. However, you won't see a direct list of who actually has your number.\n\n2. **Profile and Status Visibility**: WhatsApp settings for profile picture and status updates are typically set to \"My Contacts\" by default. If certain people can see your profile picture or status updates and respond, it's likely they have your number saved.\n\nIf you're concerned about privacy, consider setting your profile and status privacy settings to control who can see your information.",
